sourceMeaningMnemonic: A <radical>crab</radical> moves a <radical>stone</radical> because he is playing the game <kanji>Go</kanji>. You know this game, right? You put black or white stones on a board until you win the game. This is the Japanese game known as Go. This crab is pretty good.
meaningInfo: Look at this crab placing stones on the Go board. Hear them click and clack as the crab places them with expert precision.
readingMnemonic: <kanji>Go</kanji> is pronounced <reading>Go</reading> (<ja>ご</ja>) in Japanese, too. How convenient is that? Like, super convenient. So easy even a crab could remember!
